Quick note from the A/V department. Most of the equipment we have on site is able to be used for various things like photoshoots or audio recording. You're welcome to it, and I'm happy to give any pointers if needed. 

That said, if you use any of the more complex equipment, such as studio lighting, please please be sure to return everything to the state you found it in. This includes any of the light modifiers, remote triggers (esp. for batteries), etc. 

Let me know if you ever have questions on any of this stuff. Happy to help, and really excited that we are able to put all this equipment to good use. 

Thanks!
